  user_id UUID REFERENCES users(id),
  workout_type VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
  duration INTERVAL
);

    user_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    username VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    email VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
    age INT,
    gender VARCHAR(10),
    created_at TIMESTAMP NOT NULL
);

CREATE TABLE activities (
    activity_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    activity_name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    description TEXT,
    difficulty_level INT,
    created_at TIMESTAMP NOT NULL
);

CREATE TABLE workouts (
    workout_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    user_id UUID NOT NULL,
    activity_id INT NOT NULL,
    start_time TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
    end_time TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
    duration INTERVAL,
    calories_burned INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (user_id) REFERENCES users(user_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (activity_id) REFERENCES activities(activity_id)
);

CREATE TABLE goals (
    goal_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    user_id UUID NOT NULL,
    goal_name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    target INT,
    deadline DATE,
    created_at TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,

CREATE TABLE goals (
    goal_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    user_id UUID NOT NULL,
    goal_name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    target INT,
    deadline DATE,
    created_at TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
    completed BOOLEAN NOT NULL
);

CREATE TABLE progress (
    progress_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    goal_id INT NOT NULL,
    progress INT,
    date DATE NOT NULL,
    FOREIGN KEY (goal_id) REFERENCES goals(goal_id)
);

CREATE TABLE activities (
    activity_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    activity_name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    description TEXT,
    difficulty_level INT,
    created_at TIMESTAMP NOT NULL
);</t><stat>INSERT INTO users (user_id, username, email, age, gender, created_at) SELECT uuid_generate_v4(), 'Alice', 'alice@example.com', 30, 'Female', NOW();</stat><divider><t>CREATE TABLE users (
    user_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    username VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    email VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
    age INT,
    gender VARCHAR(10),
    created_at TIMESTAMP NOT NULL
);

CREATE TABLE workouts (
    workout_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    user_id UUID NOT NULL,
    activity_id INT NOT NULL,
    start_time TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
    end_time TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
    duration INTERVAL,
    calories_burned INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (user_id) REFERENCES users(user_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (activity_id) REFERENCES activities(activity_id)
);

    user_id UUID NOT NULL,
    goal_name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    target INT,
    deadline DATE,
    created_at TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
    completed BOOLEAN NOT NULL
);

CREATE TABLE users (
    user_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    username VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    email VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
    age INT,
    gender VARCHAR(10),
    created_at TIMESTAMP NOT NULL
);</t><stat>insert into users (user_id, username, email, age, gender, created_at) select uuid_generate_v4(), 'alice', 'alice@example.com', 30, 'female', now();</stat><divider><t>CREATE TABLE activities (

CREATE TABLE goals (
    goal_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    user_id UUID NOT NULL,
    goal_name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    target INT,
    deadline DATE,
    created_at TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,

CREATE TABLE users (
    user_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    username VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    email VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
    age INT,
    gender VARCHAR(10),
    created_at TIMESTAMP NOT NULL
);

CREATE TABLE workouts (
    workout_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    user_id UUID NOT NULL,
    activity_id INT NOT NULL,
    start_time TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
    end_time TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
    duration INTERVAL,
    calories_burned INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (user_id) REFERENCES users(user_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (activity_id) REFERENCES activities(activity_id)
);

CREATE TABLE progress (
    progress_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    goal_id INT NOT NULL,
    progress INT,
    date DATE NOT NULL,
    FOREIGN KEY (goal_id) REFERENCES goals(goal_id)

    start_time TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
    end_time TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
    duration INTERVAL,
    calories_burned INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (user_id) REFERENCES users(user_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (activity_id) REFERENCES activities(activity_id)
);

    user_id UUID NOT NULL,
    activity_id INT NOT NULL,
    start_time TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
    end_time TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
    duration INTERVAL,
    calories_burned INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (user_id) REFERENCES users(user_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (activity_id) REFERENCES activities(activity_id)
);

CREATE TABLE users (
    user_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    username VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    email VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
    age INT,
    gender VARCHAR(10),
    created_at TIMESTAMP NOT NULL
);

CREATE TABLE progress (
    progress_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    goal_id INT NOT NULL,
    progress INT,
    date DATE NOT NULL,
    FOREIGN KEY (goal_id) REFERENCES goals(goal_id)
);</t><stat>INSERT INTO users (user_id, username, email, age, gender, created_at) SELECT uuid_generate_v4(), 'Alice', 'alice@example.com', 30, 'Female', NOW();</stat><divider><t>CREATE TABLE goals (

    created_at TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
    completed BOOLEAN NOT NULL
);

    activity_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,

    user_id UUID NOT NULL,
    activity_id INT NOT NULL,
    start_time TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
    end_time TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
    duration INTERVAL,
    calories_burned INT,

    FOREIGN KEY (activity_id) REFERENCES activities(activity_id)

CREATE TABLE goals (
    goal_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    user_id UUID NOT NULL,
    goal_name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    target INT,
    deadline DATE,
    created_at TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
    completed BOOLEAN NOT NULL
);

    goal_name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    target INT,
    deadline DATE,
    created_at TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
    completed BOOLEAN NOT NULL
);

    user_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    username VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    email VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,

    gender VARCHAR(10),
    created_at TIMESTAMP NOT NULL
);

    workout_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    user_id UUID NOT NULL,
    activity_id INT NOT NULL,
    start_time TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
    end_time TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
    duration INTERVAL,
    calories_burned INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (user_id) REFERENCES users(user_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (activity_id) REFERENCES activities(activity_id)
);

CREATE TABLE activities (
    activity_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    activity_name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    description TEXT,
    difficulty_level INT,
    created_at TIMESTAMP NOT NULL
);

CREATE TABLE users (
    user_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    username VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    email VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
    age INT,
    gender VARCHAR(10),
    created_at TIMESTAMP NOT NULL
);</t><stat>INSERT INTO activities (activity_id, activity_name, description, difficulty_level, created_at) SELECT DEFAULT, 'Running', 'Running in the park', 3, NOW();</stat><divider><t>CREATE TABLE goals (
    goal_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    user_id UUID NOT NULL,
    goal_name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    target INT,
    deadline DATE,
    created_at TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
    completed BOOLEAN NOT NULL
);

CREATE TABLE progress (
    progress_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    goal_id INT NOT NULL,
    progress INT,
    date DATE NOT NULL,
    FOREIGN KEY (goal_id) REFERENCES goals(goal_id)
);

    activity_name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    description TEXT,
    difficulty_level INT,
    created_at TIMESTAMP NOT NULL
);

CREATE TABLE workouts (
    workout_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    user_id UUID NOT NULL,
    activity_id INT NOT NULL,
    start_time TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
    end_time TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
    duration INTERVAL,
    calories_burned INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (user_id) REFERENCES users(user_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (activity_id) REFERENCES activities(activity_id)
);

CREATE TABLE goals (
    goal_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    user_id UUID NOT NULL,
    goal_name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    target INT,
    deadline DATE,
    created_at TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
    completed BOOLEAN NOT NULL
);</t><stat>insert into goals (goal_id, user_id, goal_name, target, deadline, created_at, completed) select default, (select user_id from users order by random() limit 1), 'run 5k', 5000, '2023-01-01', now(), false;</stat><divider><t>CREATE TABLE users (
    user_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    username VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    email VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
    age INT,
    gender VARCHAR(10),
    created_at TIMESTAMP NOT NULL
);

CREATE TABLE progress (
    progress_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    goal_id INT NOT NULL,
    progress INT,
    date DATE NOT NULL,
    FOREIGN KEY (goal_id) REFERENCES goals(goal_id)
);

    user_id UUID NOT NULL,
    activity_id INT NOT NULL,
    start_time TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
    end_time TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
    duration INTERVAL,
    calories_burned INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (user_id) REFERENCES users(user_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (activity_id) REFERENCES activities(activity_id)
);

CREATE TABLE progress (
    progress_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    goal_id INT NOT NULL,
    progress INT,
    date DATE NOT NULL,
    FOREIGN KEY (goal_id) REFERENCES goals(goal_id)
);

CREATE TABLE goals (
    goal_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    user_id UUID NOT NULL,
    goal_name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    target INT,
    deadline DATE,
    created_at TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
    completed BOOLEAN NOT NULL
);

CREATE TABLE activities (
    activity_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    activity_name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    description TEXT,
    difficulty_level INT,
    created_at TIMESTAMP NOT NULL
);</t><stat>INSERT INTO progress (progress_id, goal_id, progress, date) SELECT DEFAULT, (SELECT goal_id FROM goals ORDER BY random() LIMIT 1), 2500, '2022-06-30';</stat><divider><t>CREATE TABLE users (
    user_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    username VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    email VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
    age INT,
    gender VARCHAR(10),
    created_at TIMESTAMP NOT NULL
);

    username VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    email VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
    age INT,
    gender VARCHAR(10),
    created_at TIMESTAMP NOT NULL
);

CREATE TABLE workouts (
    workout_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    user_id UUID NOT NULL,
    activity_id INT NOT NULL,
    start_time TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
    end_time TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
    duration INTERVAL,
    calories_burned INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (user_id) REFERENCES users(user_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (activity_id) REFERENCES activities(activity_id)
);</t><stat>insert into progress (progress_id, goal_id, progress, date) select default, (select goal_id from goals order by random() limit 1), 2500, '2022-06-30';</stat><divider><t>CREATE TABLE goals (
    goal_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    user_id UUID NOT NULL,
    goal_name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    target INT,
    deadline DATE,
    created_at TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
    completed BOOLEAN NOT NULL
);

CREATE TABLE activities (
    activity_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    activity_name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    description TEXT,
    difficulty_level INT,
    created_at TIMESTAMP NOT NULL
);

CREATE TABLE progress (
    progress_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    goal_id INT NOT NULL,
    progress INT,
    date DATE NOT NULL,
    FOREIGN KEY (goal_id) REFERENCES goals(goal_id)
);

    goal_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    user_id UUID NOT NULL,
    goal_name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    target INT,
    deadline DATE,
    created_at TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
    completed BOOLEAN NOT NULL
);

CREATE TABLE workouts (
    workout_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    user_id UUID NOT NULL,
    activity_id INT NOT NULL,
    start_time TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
    end_time TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
    duration INTERVAL,
    calories_burned INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (user_id) REFERENCES users(user_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (activity_id) REFERENCES activities(activity_id)
);

CREATE TABLE users (
    user_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    username VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    email VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
    age INT,
    gender VARCHAR(10),
    created_at TIMESTAMP NOT NULL
);

    activity_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    activity_name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    description TEXT,
    difficulty_level INT,
    created_at TIMESTAMP NOT NULL
